values.Item: What is the date of receipt of appointment as BLO?

Whether training imparted from the end of ERO and duties and
Responsibilities of BLO explained? Please mention date.

Whether the relevant part(s) of the current Electoral Roll received along
with all supplements?

Whether the electoral roll part(s) including cover page(s) thoroughly
scrutinized to find out defects?

Whether part-wise register is opened to record such defects, other
inputs of field verification & corresponding field observations and
all other activities?

Whether the BLO interacts with local people particularly elder
electors, local elected representatives & representatives of political
parties on quarterly basis to find out dead and shifted electors,
eligible electors not yet enrolled and any other defects?

Whether the names of prominent personalities of the locality
exist in the roll? If not, whether the same has been reported to
the ERO?

Whether a letter box is placed at his place of posting or at some
other office/institution, convenient for the electors (with the prior
approval of ERO) to receive information/complaints/suggestions
and whether the same has been communicated to the local elected
and political representatives? Please mention the location.

values.What are the steps taken to inform the e:
Whether details of addition/correction/deletions made during
continuous revision process are collected from ERO on quarterly
basis?

Whether local Birth & Death Registration Office visited on
quarterly basis during post revision period and probable dead
electors identified checking their death register?

values.Item:
Whether field enquiry conducted on quarterly basis during post
revision period to defect dead and shifted electors and verify
information received from various sources in this regard as well as
in regard to defects of the electoral roll?

Whether field enquiry reports in relation to sl.no.12 submitted
in the format prescribed by the ERO? Also mention date(s) of
submission of reports.

Whether notice for hearing into such enquiry reports served in
time?

Whether defects related to particulars of cover page, i.e., polling area,
section details, polling station address, etc. detected and rationalization
of polling area felt necessary? If so, whether
report submitted to ERO after interacting with local people and field
verification?

Whether de-duplication, validation reports (related to Eroll Clean
Software), list of Non-EPIC Electors, etc., reports received from
ERO? Please mention date.
Whether field enquiry conducted to verify the aforesaid reports?

Whether enquiry reports related to Sl.No.17 submitted in the
format prescribed by ERO? Also mention date(s) of submission of
reports?

Whether working copy of photo electoral roll received from ERO for
field verification of images? Please mention date. (Applicable for ACs
going for publication of photo roll for the 1st time)
Whether field verification related to Sl.No.19 completed?

Whether report regarding image verification submitted? Please
mention date.

values.What are the initiatives taken to inform:
What are the steps taken to guide people filing claims and
objections?

Whether meeting of Gram Sansad/Ward/Booth or the like
organized in connection with revision of electoral roll attended by
the BLO?

Whether Form 6, 7, 8, 8A received by the Designated Officers
during revision period handed over to the BLO by the ERO for
field enquiry? Please mention date and number of forms received.

Whether field enquiry held into such 6, 7, 8, 8A and enquiry
report prepared in the format prescribed by the ERO?

values.Item:
Whether enquiry report noted in sl.no.26 submitted? Please
mention date.

Whether houses of Non-EPIC electors visited to inform the
electors about date, time and venue of photo-taking programme?

Whether Form 001/002/004 supplied to the elector during home
visit and whether assistance provided to fill up the form?

Whether the BLO remained present at the photo-taking venue on
the day of photo taking to assist electors?

Please mention the number of EPIC received from ERO for
distribution and number of EPICs delivered at elector’s address.

Whether Signature/LTI of elector obtained as an
acknowledgement of receipt of the EPIC?

Date(s) of verification of the register as mentioned in sl.no.5 by
the authorized representative of ERO.
